hours: Monday: 8:00 AM - 3:00 PM Tuesday: 8:00 AM - 3:00 PM Wednesday: 8:00 AM - 3:00 PM Thursday: 8:00 AM - 3:00 PM Friday: 8:00 AM - 3:00 PM
materials: Plastic #1 (PETE); Plastic #2 (HDPE); Plastic #2 (Color HDPE); Plastic #3 (PVC); Plastic #4 (LDPE); Plastic #5 (Polypropylene); Plastic #7; Aluminum Cans; Glass (Brown); Cardboard; Catalogs; Chipboard; Glass (Clear); Computer Paper; Electronics; Gift Boxes; Glass (Green); Greeting Cards; Magazines; Paper (Mixed); Newspapers; Unused Paint; Paperboard; Televisions; Tin or Steel Cans; Used Motor Oil; Office Paper
notes: The Street Department is also open on the first and third Saturdays of each month from 8:00 a.m.  noon to accept glass, plastic, cardboard, paper, metal, televisions, electronic equipment, paint, motor oil, trash, leaves, and grass clippings. No brush or tree limbs, construction materials, tires or bulk items are accepted on Saturdays.

name: Wildcat Creek Solid Waste Management HHW Drop-off Site
description: Wildcat Creek Solid Waste Management HHW Drop-off Site
hours: Monday: 9:00 AM - 3:00 PM Tuesday: 9:00 AM - 3:00 PM Thursday: 9:00 AM - 3:00 PM Friday: 9:00 AM - 3:00 PM
materials: Antifreeze; Brake Fluid; Lead Acid (Pb) Batteries; Compact Fluorescent Lights; Fertilizer; Fluorescent Lamps/Tubes; Fungicides; Herbicides; Household Cleaners; Insecticides; Mercury Containing Items; Ni-Cd Batteries; Other Batteries; Latex Paint; Paint Thinner; Pesticides; Pool Chemicals; Batteries (Rechargeable); Solvents; Transmission Fluid; Used Motor Oil; Oil Filters
notes: Services are restricted to Clinton County residents who are asked to call ahead to schedule a drop-off appointment and learn how to properly transport materials. Also open the first Saturday of each month 9 AM - 12 PM.
